rds accomplishing a squad‚Äôs mission. You use your seniority to maximize team performance. How to succeed You are seen and acknowledged by your colleagues as a competent engineer Have a proven ability to bring out the best in people and drive the team forward Have great analytical skills and have a conceptual / architectural understanding Are experienced with test driven development & test automation Have a Growth mind-set and a pragmatic thinking Are able to bring all ideas/opinions to one conclusion to help make decisions Are up to date with new technology and have a deep understanding of when to use it Have 5 years of experience as a lead developer in both Java and JavaScript based projects Are a great storyteller and able to adapt your style depending on your audience Are humble in approach and not afraid to be wrong Are proud of what you do and enjoy sharing this with your external network Are experienced in Agile methodologies Are fluent in English speaking and writing Your benefits Working at our company means working in a dynamic and international setting. Individual development for our employees is very important and that is why we offer excellent courses and programs. You will become a member of the IT Management team. Diva behaviour is not tolerated, neither is underperformance. We only hire people with exceptional talents. To give you an idea, we will tell you about the benefits of working at ING: A job from 36 to 40 hours that fits your schedule to balance work and private life A salary tailored to your qualities and experience Travel reimbursement 24 vacation days with 36-hour work week. (or 27 days with 40) Pension scheme 13th month salary Individual Savings Contribution (BIS), 3.5% of yourgross annual salary 8% Holiday payment Personal growth and challenging work with endless possibilities An informal working environment with innovative colleagues Work Agile, so new ideas come to life faster Questions? Contact the recruiter attached to the advertisement for more information. Want to apply directly? Please upload your CV and motivation letter by clicking the ‚ÄúApply‚Äù button. About us With around 52,000 employees and operations in approximately 40 countries, there is no shortage of opportunities for people with initiative who want to make a diÔ¨Äerence. We hire smart people like you for your potential, not your past. Our biggest expectation is that you‚Äôll stay curious. Keep learning. Take on more responsibility. In return, we‚Äôll back you to develop into an even more awesome version of yourself. If you want to work at the cutting edge of what‚Äôs possible, surrounded by progressive, inspiring and supportive colleagues, there is no better place to invest your talents than at ING. Join us. Apply today. Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Recruiter Engineer Java Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', '0', '', null, null, 'IT Chapter Lead', null, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10135892-it-chapter-lead');
INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('a79b834a-c88a-4860-b87f-047471b563ff', 'Research bioinformatician Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 26 augustus Erasmus MC Job description The Department of Immunology conducts state-of-the-art basic and translational research in the field of human and medical immunology. The research is focused on the biology and treatment of diseases such as Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), COVID-19 and immune-related cancers. The Department of Immunology is looking for a highly motivated (bio)informatician to develop workflow and tools and to create and support a bioinformatics environment that strongly contributes to innovative computational immunology research. The bioinformatician will collaborate in a multi-disciplinary team and should contribute significantly to solve general and specific questions within immunology research fields using his/her bioinformatics expertise. To accomplish this task new in-house whole genome, transcriptome, proteome and single cell data sets, as well as, publicly available data sets will be processed, interrogated and visualized. Work environment The Department of Immunology performs cutting edge basic and translational research, participates in patient care by performing laboratory diagnostics (Laboratory for Medical Immunology) and supporting Clinical Immunology, and performs a wide range of educational activities. The Department has an international environment with employees and students from many countries. The bioinformatician will be supervised by Dr. ir. Harmen van de Werken and work together with Prof. Dr. Peter Katsikis. Qualifications and skills You have a BSc or MSc degree in informatics, bioinformatics or related field and two years of experience in (bio)informatics, statistics or computer science. You have demonstrated excellent programming skills in Python or Perl and preferably in Java and in workflow management systems such as Nextflow and Snakemake. You have proven experience in relational databases management systems, such as MySQL or PostgreSQL, in statistical computer language R and in Linux operating system. Experience in analyzing next-generation sequencing data or mass spectrometry-based proteomics data is a prerequisite. You have strong analytical and problem solving skills, excellent communication and technical writing skills and are able to work independently and as member of a bioinformatics team. A background in cancer biology is a strong plus. Before you apply please check our conditions for employment. Terms of employment As a research bioinformatician you will be offered a temporary contract for two years that can be extended. The gross monthly salary amounts a maximum of ‚Ç¨ 3712,- (scale 8), depending on your level of education and experience. In addition, we offer an end-of-year bonus of 8.3% and an individual travel expense budget. The terms of employment are according to the Collective Bargaining Agreement for Dutch University Medical Centers (CAO UMC). Information and application For more information about this position, please contact Dr. Harmen van de Werken, e-mail: h.vandewerken@erasmusmc.nl, or Prof. Dr. Peter Katsikis email: p.katsikis@erasmusmc.nl. For queries regarding your application, please contact Jerry Chandansingh, Recruiter, by phone number: +31 (0)6 500 310 06. If you are excited by the thought of this position and would like to apply, please do so by using the application form on our website. No agencies please. Uren: 36 hours Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Recruiter Java Linux Parttime Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', '0', '', null, null, 'Research bioinformatician', null, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10538352-research-bioinformatician');
