e System Engineers kunnen worden, met een goede domeinkennis en een brede kijk op systemen. Of wellicht ben jij de engineer met technisch inzicht en overzicht en ga je voor een rol als Software Architect. Onderscheid je je juist als een organisator? Dan kan een carri√®re pad in de richting van Agile ScrumMaster of projectleider bij je passen. Thales offers you een interessante baan binnen een leuk team in een internationale hightech omgeving; ruimte en aandacht voor persoonlijke ontwikkeling en eigen initiatief; de mogelijkheid om te groeien binnen de organisatie, bijvoorbeeld op technisch-/management-/commercieel- of internationaal vlak; een open en flexibele werkomgeving waarbij een goede work-life balance belangrijk is; een fijne werkplek in ‚ÄòHet beste gebouw van Nederland‚Äô (Public‚Äôs ChoiceAward 2015) met onze eigen Starbucks corner; goede arbeidsvoorwaarden, met onder andere 40 vakantiedagen per jaar. Interested?. Direct solliciteren? Gebruik dan je eigen, persoonlijke profiel om jouw interesse aan ons kenbaar te maken en kies voor ‚ÄòApply now‚Äô. At Thales we provide CAREERS and not only jobs. With Thales employing 80,000 employees in 68 countries our mobility policy enables thousands of employees each year to develop their careers at home and abroad, in their existing areas of expertise or by branching out into new fields. Together we believe that embracing flexibility is a smarter way of working. Great journeys start here, apply now! Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Projectleider Front-end developer Architect Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', '0', '', null, null, 'Lead Front-End Developer', null, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10391229-lead-front-end-developer');
INSERT INTO public.vacancy (id, about, broker, hours, location, posting_date, salary, title, vacancy_number, vacancyurl) VALUES ('1f764b5d-8471-4a73-a37f-f457f92350a6', 'SOFTWARE ENGINEER C++ Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 11 augustus Thales In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our architects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible. SOFTWARE ENGINEER C++ To strengthen our Thales (Hengelo) team within the cluster Above Water Warfare (AWW) Fire Control Systems (FCS), we are looking for enthusiastic and motivated SOFTWARE ENGINEERS C++ with a passion for technology and the ambition to pursue a career in a high-tech environment. About the job As a Software Engineer you work in a multidisciplinary and self-organizing Agile-Scrum team. In addition to software product development, our teams are fully responsible for a various aspects such as requirements analysis, design, architecture, testing, validation and regular product demonstrations. The use of high-tech techniques and software development methods is important. The Fire Control System product development is based both on Java and C++ and is supported by a modern development environment. Large parts of the Missile Fire Control and Gun Fire Control domains are based on the C++ technology stack. The Above Water Warfare Fire Control System (AWW-FCS) protects ships and other units from above-water threats, which are becoming faster, smarter and more complex. To this end, it uses Thales'' next-generation dual-band radar suite, which integrates an Active Phased-Array Radar (APAR) in the X-band with a Sea Master 400 radar in the S-band Anti-ship missiles go three to five times faster than sound with increasingly complex behavior. When several of these threats come up against them simultaneously, it becomes increasingly difficult for human operators to take efficient and effective protection measures. The AWW-FCS provides the necessary information to make the right decision within seconds. With a combination of a new generation of sensors and an intelligent Fire Control System, it continuously assesses which methods are best suited to engage the detected threat. A Fire Control System combines the radar and the intelligent algorithm which is designed to assist a ranged weapon system in targeting, tracking and hitting its target. About you Are you passionate about technology and would you like to work on the high-tech architecture of Naval Fire Control Systems? If so, you are the person we are looking for. You are a talented and experienced C++ Software Engineer who likes to cooperate in the design and development of software solutions within our complex Naval domain. You have a solid background in software development using modern development tools and methods. You are capable of rapidly mastering new domains and techniques. You graduated at HBO or WO level in the field of Information or Computer Science. As a person, you are creative, open and flexible and able to operate as an enthusiastic team player. In addition, you are result-oriented, show initiative and able to communicate clearly. An excellent command of the Dutch and English languages, both spoken and written, is essential in order to perform well in this role. Knowledge of and experience with the following tools and techniques are important: ‚Ä¢ Agile/Scrum software development ‚Ä¢ C++, CMake, real-time software development ‚Ä¢ Continuous Integration & Delivery ‚Ä¢ Jenkins, Nexus, Maven, GIT, BitBucket ‚Ä¢ Unit Testing, Test Automation, Google-Test ‚Ä¢ MatLab, SimuLink (pr√©) In addition, we will offer you the opportunity to further your career within Thales'' high-tech environment. You could become one of our future System Engineers, with extensive domain expertise and 